yafc 1.1.1 Copyright (C) 1998-2001 Martin Hedenfalk <mhe@home.se>.
This is yet another FTP client.  Usage:
 yafc [options] [[proto://][user[:password]@]hostname[:port][/directory] ...]
 proto can be either 'ftp' or 'ssh'
Options:
  -a, --anon        (*) anonymous login
  -d, --debug           print all commands sent to/from server
  -D, --dump-rc         prints the default config file to stdout
  -m, --mechanism=MECH
                    (*) try MECH as security mechanism(s)
  -n, --norc            don't parse config file
  -p, --noproxy     (*) don't connect via proxy
  -q, --quiet           don't print the yafc welcome message
  -r, --rcfile=FILE     use other config file instead of ~/.yafc/yafcrc
  -t, --trace[=FILE]    use a trace file (mainly for debugging)
               if FILE specified, use it instead of ~/.yafc/trace/trace.<pid>
  -u, --noauto      (*) disable autologin
  -U, --noalias     (*) disable bookmark alias lookup and abbreviation
  -v, --verbose         print all replies from server
  -w, --wait=TIME       use a different wait time for reconnecting
  -W, --workdir=DIR     use a different working directory (instead of ~/.yafc)
  -V, --version         print version information and quit
  -h, --help            print this help and quit

(*) only applies for login to host specified on the command line

Report bugs to <yafc-devel@lists.sourceforge.net>

